<h2 id="best-spot-on-flea-treatment-for-cats">Whats The Best Spot-on Flea Treatment For Cats?</h2>
<p>Because they have long-lasting effects and treat fleas thoroughly, these are some of the most popular and effective flea treatments available.</p>
<p>You apply these medications to the back of your cats neck, where they cant lick off the gel.</p>
<p>These treatments start working within 12 hours and usually contain insect growth regulators, which stop flea growth and reproduction.</p>
