<h2 id="best-flea-collar-for-cats">Whats The Best Flea Collar For Cats?</h2>
<p>Flea collars release small amounts of insecticide chemicals, which spread over your cats body and absorb into their skin, killing existing parasites and helping your cat to repel new fleas.</p>
<p>They demand little to no human intervention, working around the clock to protect your cat. This makes them an extraordinarily convenient and low-maintenance option.</p>
<p>However, the possible side effects of using flea collars often outweigh the convenience of this flea control option. Some flea collars have been associated with problems in cats, especially if they are curious chewers and ingest part of the collar.</p>
