<header class="comment-meta comment-author vcard">
<img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/c0736461b3290ceab9eda0c473944143?s=44&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/c0736461b3290ceab9eda0c473944143?s=88&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-44 photo' height='44' width='44' loading='lazy' decoding='async' /><cite><b class="fn">S. Britt</b> </cite><a href="https://allaboutcats.com/best-flea-treatment-for-cats#comment-88382"><time datetime="2022-09-07T14:21:35+00:00">Sep 7, 2022 at 2:21 pm</time></a> </header>
<section class="comment-content comment">
<p>My cat received flea medicine monthly as recommended by vet. It worked 100%, but my cat ran away from me when it was time for his Revolution med. He got cancer of tongue, drooled, lost fur, lost use of hind legs and had to be put down. I would not use meds again for any cat.</p>
</section>
<div class="reply">
<a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-88382' data-commentid="88382" data-postid="3355" data-belowelement="comment-88382" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to S. Britt" aria-label='Reply to S. Britt'>Reply</a> <span>&darr;</span> </div>
</article>
<ol class="children">
<li class="comment byuser comment-author-mcrustawildernesscat-com bypostauthor even depth-2" id="li-comment-88433">
<article id="comment-88433" class="comment">
<header class="comment-meta comment-author vcard">
<img alt='small mallory photo' src='https://allaboutcats.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/cropped-Small-pfp-44x44.jpg' srcset='https://allaboutcats.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/cropped-Small-pfp-88x88.jpg 2x' class='avatar avatar-44 photo' height='44' width='44' loading='lazy' decoding='async' /><cite><b class="fn"><a href='https://www.wildernesscat.com/' rel='external nofollow ugc' class='url'>Mallory Crusta</a></b> <span>Post author</span></cite><a href="https://allaboutcats.com/best-flea-treatment-for-cats#comment-88433"><time datetime="2022-09-08T00:59:45+00:00">Sep 8, 2022 at 12:59 am</time></a> </header>
<section class="comment-content comment">
<p>What a terrible story. Thank you for sharing, though I would not immediately assume that the Revolution was responsible for your cat&#8217;s illness. This would be worth further investigation if possible, but I understand that you wouldn&#8217;t want to use this medication again for another cat. I&#8217;d also feel quite cautious about any flea medication, especially collars and topicals, due to the frequency of adverse effects. I&#8217;m sorry for the loss of your cat.</p>
</section>
